longBusinessSummary: GA eXpress, Inc. engages in the development and licensing of computer software and related software-consulting services. The company's primary products offer data connectivity that enables businesses to connect legacy applications and databases to e-business exchanges and trading partners over the Internet. It has developed a portfolio of software products and services under the name of ePathÂ. The ePathÂ products include a suite of middleware, eToolsÂ that are focused on data access and connectivity for the MultiValue marketplace, and a collaborative commerce server, code named Selva Server. The company's professional services include consulting services, training-related services to customers and partners, and software maintenance services, including technical support. GA eXpress has subsidiaries in the United States, Canada, Australia, and United Kingdom. The company, formerly known as General Automation, Inc., is based in Vancouver, Canada.
